cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the application of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for detecting prohibited items in X-ray security imagery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of synthetic imagery, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it relates to security imaging. The use of CNNs and large volumes of data also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the evaluation of detection performance, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
